# Frontend Rules

## Framework
- Next.js 14 App Router
- Server Components by default
- Client Components only when needed
- Streaming where beneficial

## Styling
- Tailwind CSS
- shadcn/ui components
- No inline styles
- Mobile-first responsive

## State
- TanStack Query for server state
- Zustand for client state
- URL state via searchParams
- No prop drilling (compose well)

## Forms
- react-hook-form + Zod
- Server actions or fetch
- Optimistic updates where safe
- Loading + error states always

## Data Fetching
- Server: direct fetch in components
- Client: TanStack Query
- Suspense boundaries
- Error boundaries

## Realtime
- WebSocket for terminal
- SSE for agent task updates
- Reconnection logic
- Backpressure handling

## Performance
- Lazy load heavy components
- Image optimization (next/image)
- Bundle analysis in CI
- Lighthouse score > 90

## Accessibility
- Semantic HTML
- ARIA where needed
- Keyboard navigation
- Focus management
- Color contrast WCAG AA

## Testing
- Component tests: Vitest + Testing Library
- E2E: Playwright
- Visual regression (V2)

## File Structure
- app/ (routes)
- components/ (shared)
- features/ (feature-specific)
- lib/ (utils, clients)
- hooks/ (custom hooks)